        "A walled holy city shared by three world religions atop millennia of history.",
        "Within one square kilometre, the Old City holds the Dome of the Rock, the Western Wall, and the Church of the Holy Sepulchre. Every stone here resonates with sacred memory spanning thousands of years.\n\nThe narrow stone lanes of the souq bustle with pilgrims, vendors, and locals in a timeless daily rhythm. Arrive at dawn to witness the city stir to life before the crowds descend.",
