        "A dramatic mesa-top fortress where Jewish rebels made their last stand against Rome in 73 CE.",
        "Rising 400 metres above the Dead Sea, Masada's plateau holds Herod's palaces, Roman-era bathhouses, and a haunting history of siege and sacrifice. The Snake Path ascent at sunrise rewards with panoramic desert views.\n\nA cable car provides easy access for those who prefer not to hike. The surrounding desert landscape glows in hues of amber and gold at golden hour.",
