        "Taroko National Park's centrepiece is a 19-kilometre gorge where sheer marble walls rise hundreds of metres above a jade-green river. Tunnels carved through living rock connect viewpoints along the Central Cross-Island Highway.\n\nThe Swallow Grotto and Tunnel of Nine Turns walking trails bring visitors face-to-face with the dramatic geology. Waterfalls cascade from clifftops and mist drifts through the canyon on cool mornings.",
